<TITLE> 'Killer' caught dead in Old Dhaka shootout with RAB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 2 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected killer was shot dead in a gunfight with Rapid Action Battalion in Old Dhaka's English Road early Tuesday. Twenty-nine year old Mamunur Rashid, alias Kala Mamun, of south Keraniganj, was a "hired killer", said Maj Mahbubul Islam of RAB-10 Lalbagh zone. Islam told bdnews24.com that acting on a tip-off they came upon a gathering of some 10-12 suspects at English Road at around 3am. The elite force, in plainclothes, challenged the group who ran away firing shots. RAB fired back, said Islam. After about 15 minutes of gunfire from both sides, the criminals fled the scene. RAB found Mamun's body on the spot. One 9mm handgun, one 6mm handgun and seven rounds of ammunition were also recovered, Islam said. RAB said Mamun was accused in at least five criminal cases including two for murder. His body was taken to Salimullah Medical College Hospital morgue for autopsy. bdn
